data.text:
Mourners dressed in their ao dai and finest satin trousers at the cremation of Thich Quang Duc in Saigon, Vietnam

A single mother surrounded by her three small children, New York City.

Permanent collection, Museum of Modern Art

Aberdeen was once a charming fishing village in Hong Kong. Diners would hire sampans to take them to Jumbo and other boat restaurants where they chose their live fish for dinner. Today Aberdeen is characterized by its sleek, glass high-rises and white yachts.
